    <body>
      <div type="page" n="163">
        <pb n="163"/>
        <ab xml:id="block_A" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F26115641-5696-4140-a029-ab0b4657cfe8.jp2/1336,1227,2813,767/max/0/default.jpg">
          WE ARE A PEOPLE in whom the past endures,<lb/>
        in whom the present is inconceivable without moments gone by.<lb/>
        The Exodus lasted a moment, a moment enduring forever.<lb/>
        What happened once upon a time happens all the time.
        </ab>
        <ab xml:id="block_B" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F26115641-5696-4140-a029-ab0b4657cfe8.jp2/1357,2432,2233,824/max/0/default.jpg">
          A THOUGHT has blown the market place away.<lb/>
        There is a song on the wind and joy in the trees.<lb/>
        Shabbat arrives in the world,<lb/>
        scattering a song in the silence of the night:<lb/>
        Eternity utters a day.
        </ab>
        <ab xml:id="block_C" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F26115641-5696-4140-a029-ab0b4657cfe8.jp2/929,6008,3611,250/max/0/default.jpg">
          More than the Jewish People has kept Shabbat, Shabbat has kept the Jewish People. Ahad Ha-Am
        </ab>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
